Yuner and Liter are promoted to admins.
As an admin, you must remember:
1. never promote or depromote people for fun.
2. never modify system files when you dont know what could happen after that.
3. make backups for every file you modified.
4. dont try any command that you dont know what could happen. Look the source
code first and make sure you can understand it.
5. make sure you understand the security here fully before you use it to 
arrange groups, domains to manage this mud.
6. drop me a mail if you crash lima by mistake.
7. be careful of system codes, those in /daemons, /secure, /std, /trans, etc..
never change them unless you know precisely what you are doing.

I believe there will be a lot of pain to be admin here. 
Take it easy and dont panic :)

stefan


